These are the database table scripts for Lampadas:

createdb.sh	creates a new, empty database
defaults.sql	populates "static" tables with default data
delete.sql	deletes all data from the database
indexes.sql	sets foreign keys and other index constraints, except for
		primary keys, which are set in the individual table scripts
load.sql	loads all tables from the /tmp directory
permissions.sql	sets proper permissions for the web server user
		(FIXME: Debian specific right now)
save.sql	backs up all tables to the /tmp directory

To create a new database, run the following scripts, in order:

createdb.sh	create tables
defaults.sql	load default data
indexes.sql	set constraints
permissions.sql	set permissions

To load a backed up database, run:

createdb.sh	create tables
load.sql	reload saved data
indexes.sql	set constraints
permissions.sql	set permissions

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

DIRECTORY LAYOUT

tables/TABLE_NAME     

	one directory per table
	
tables/TABLE_NAME/{create,insert,indexes,permissions}.sql

        "methods" to create table, indexes and permissions and initialize it
	(insert script)

defaults/

	default content for tables

defaults/TABLE_NAME/insert.sql

	script to insert default content into table
